OL,3,CPolice officer has gross misconduct
OL,4,Ccase to answer over fatal e-bike crash
OL,6,FThe Independent Office for Police
OL,7,FConduct (IOPC) said the officer has a
OL,8,Fcase to answer for gross misconduct
OL,9,Ffollowing its investigation over the
OL,10,Faccuracy of accounts he provided to
OL,11,Fcolleagues after the crash, and a
OL,12,Fmisconduct case to answer in relation
OL,13,Fto "his driving and language he used
OL,14,Fin relation to the boys at the
OL,15,Fcollision scene".
OL,17,FThe IOPC said its probe had concluded
OL,18,Fthat the van was around half a mile
OL,19,Faway from the e-bike and on a
OL,20,Fdifferent road when the fatal crash
OL,21,Fhappened.
