OL,6,FThe Crown Prosecution Service has
OL,7,Fpreviously decided not to bring any
OL,8,Fcriminal charge in relation to driving
OL,9,Fagainst the officer. That outcome is
OL,10,Fcurrently subject to the Victim's
OL,11,FRight of Review scheme, which allows a
OL,12,Fvictim or their families the ability
OL,13,Fto challenge the decision. The IOPC
OL,14,Fsaid it submitted a file of evidence
OL,15,Fto the CPS to consider an offence of
OL,16,Fdangerous driving for the driver of
OL,17,Fthe van.
